5:
*phew* That was enough walking to 
last me a week. We managed to find 
some good materials, right?
9:
Sure did. That crystal you picked up? 
Worth a small fortune.
14:
What of this shard, Evan? It's quite 
beautiful...
17:
Sorry, champ. Not all that glitters is 
gold.
25:
For a champion, you're not very 
useful...
30:
Champions are warriors! We are no 
maze-scavengers.
35:
Whoa... He's up in arms. If being a 
champion means facing fighters like 
him, I think I'll stick to scavenging.
41:
You came all the way here, Light. 
Might as well enjoy the treasure hunt. 
Oh, but...
50: Whoa! Uh... Evan?! What do we do?!
54: You'll be fine if you just stay near me.
67: No, Alk... This place isn't new... It'sâ€”
72:
Oh! This looks like where Nimbus used 
to live!
80:
Well, I don't know about HERE here, 
but we've been somewhere similar. 
These should be ruins in the Kingdom 
of Sand...
85:
What you just felt, by the way, 
was a tremor. Happens every time the 
Kaleidoscope shifts.
89:
Can you sense when tremors are 
coming?
92:
Technically speaking, I've got them 
memorized. You see, shifts in the 
shallows follow a schedule. They come
 at a set time and take you to a set 
place.
94:
As long as you stay calm and stay 
put, nothing bad will happen to you. 
That's why I brought you here. To ride 
out a tremor firsthand.
98:
Wait. You said shifts "in the shallows." 
What about deeper in?
101:
Your guess is as good as mine. Not 
many have experienced tremors in 
the depths and come back to tell the 
tale.
107:
The midways and beyond is no-
man's-land. We know next to nothing 
about the shifts there... or the 
monsters.
114:
Yeah... A long time ago. Wasn't easy, 
making it back.
117:
Well, wouldn't be an adventure with 
no danger, I guess... Wonder if there's 
an end to the Kaleidoscope. I kind of 
want to see it.
120:
Can't fault you for that...
Brace yourselves. Another tremor's 
coming.
131:
Think that's enough exploring for 
today. Next time, I'll bring you when 
the Kaleidoscope's a little more stable.
136:
Sounds good to me. Maybe we can 
give the midways a try.
140:
Evan. Do you think there's hope now? 
Of finding what you lost.
146:
Maybe. All I know is I've regained the 
strength to try.
149:
And that's thanks to you guys... 
I'll never forget it.
